Quote: Their reception has been variable; with the kingites, it has been very hearty; but with others they are looked upon as a lot of idle fools, "Nui Nui Mungarie and Porangi," who would do much better by staying at home, cultivating the soil, and looking after their stock, than wasting their time in gossiping expeditions over the country.
